      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a superlative example of high-revving precision, featuring the iconic S54B32 3.2L inline-six engine with individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 420G six-speed manual gearbox and a variable M differential lock, ensuring linear power delivery and exceptional lateral grip. This chassis exhibits zero subframe fatigue and retains its factory-spec suspension geometry for an uncompromised, analog driving experience. Meticulously maintained with a documented service history, the valvetrain remains quiet and the compression is within factory tolerances, making this a concours-ready specimen for the serious collector.",
